==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scotist
<hw>Sco"tist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld>
<def>A follower of (Joannes) Duns <etsep>Scotus</etsep>, the Franciscan
scholastic (<it>d.</it> 1308), who maintained certain doctrines in
philosophy and theology, in opposition to the <contr>Thomists</contr>,
or followers of Thomas Aquinas, the Dominican scholastic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

